INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '3e6c4cec-73b6-4a75-bb7a-f32709bb8451',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Lock Down Your React Repo: Prettier, Husky, and tsc in CI$escape$,
  $escape$Shipping broken types or inconsistently formatted JSX wastes review cycles. A three-layer quality gate catches issues before they hit CI or your teammates.

First, Prettier handles formatting so nobody debates brace style in reviews — configure it with `singleQuote: true` and `jsxSingleQuote: false` for idiomatic React output.

Second, Husky + lint-staged runs checks only on staged files, keeping the pre-commit hook fast. Wire it to run `prettier --write` and `eslint --fix` on `*.{ts,tsx}` files so every commit is clean without blocking your flow.

Third — the one most React projects skip — run `tsc --noEmit` in CI, not just locally. This catches broken prop types, missing generics in custom hooks, and incorrect `useRef<T>` typings that eslint won't surface. Pair it with `"strict": true` in tsconfig for full coverage.

The payoff: type errors stay out of PRs, formatting is never a comment, and broken component contracts get caught in 30 seconds instead of production.$escape$,
  $escape$// .lintstagedrc.js
module.exports = {
  '*.{ts,tsx}': [
    'prettier --write',
    'eslint --fix --max-warnings=0',
  ],
};

// package.json (scripts)
{
  "type-check": "tsc --noEmit",
  "prepare": "husky install"
}

// .husky/pre-commit
npx lint-staged$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
